<br>
Let me paint you a picture, there is a large hallway connecting the regular area of ToV and the North Wing.  The hallway is somewhat narrow (relatively speaking).  Sitting smack dab in the middle of the hallway is Aaryonar.  You cannot go around him.  You cannot go over him.  You cannot go under him.  He is KOS to everybody and the only way past him is to kill him.  THAT is why he was made to be the criteria to getting into a Rotation.  Aaryonar is a monster.  He is extremely powerful and due to some other little things designed with this encounter, he is very difficult.  Now if you are not able to kill Aaryonar, the ONLY way you can reach the North Wing is to follow after a guild who HAS killed Aaryonar.<br>
<br>
