<br>
Finally, let me make this perfectly clear.  Rotations were NEVER created to lock certain people/guilds out of a zone.  They were created to help reduce tensions and feelings of ill will toward each other.  When your turn comes up on a Rotation, you don't need to worry that another Guild will get there before you, train you etc.  You do not need to get up at an absurd time of day in order to &quot;hold&quot; the zone and &quot;camp&quot; the named mobs.  Rotations were merely a gentleman's agreement between the people who were capable of killing/clearing things in an effort to keep things civil between all parties.<br>
